-- Ireland Blyth of Mauritius Second-Quarter Sales Rise 19%; Profit Plunges
-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 2011-02-08T05:20:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-08/ireland-blyth-of-mauritius-second-quarter-sales-rise-19-profit-plunges.html
  Ireland Blyth Ltd ., a Mauritian
logistics and retail copmany, said profit for the second quarter
through December fell to 149.4 million rupees from 1.05 billion
rupees.  Revenue increased 19% to 4.3 billion rupees, the company
said in a statement published on the website of the Port Louis-
based Stock Exchange of Mauritius today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis at 
 kbhuckory@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
